The Management of Kano Zoological Garden has deployed a team of experts to capture the escaped lion which according to them would still be within the Garden.<img class="size-full wp-image-1267324 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=640%2C427&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="427" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?w=1314&amp;ssl=1 1314w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=300%2C200&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=768%2C512&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=1024%2C683&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=58%2C39&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=260%2C173&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=195%2C130&amp;ssl=1 195w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=115%2C77&amp;ssl=1 115w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/lion.jpg?resize=560%2C373&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Managing Director of the Zoo, Alhaji Saidu Gwadabe disclosed this in an interview with News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Kano on Sunday. He said the experts were armed with necessary weapons to ensure the success of the operation as well as the safety of their lives and the residents of the area. He said the team would do everything possible to capture the escaped animal alive. Troops rescue 4 more abducted  students in Kaduna(Opens in a new browser tab) “We don’t want to kill the lion unless it becomes the last option as they can shot it to make it unconscious.” He said the operation which started on Saturday night had to be suspended around 11 p.m. because of the darkness of the bush where it was currently hiding in the zoo. He, however, expressed hope that the operation would be successful as the lion had not destroyed or harmed anyone. NAN reports that the entire zoo road which is one of the busiest roads in the city had since been deserted since the incident happened on Saturday. (NAN) Vanguard The Management of Kano Zoological Garden has deployed a team of experts to capture the escaped lion which is said to still be within the Garden. October 20, 2019 In "News" There was panic on Saturday night around Zoo road in Kano metropolis when a lion escaped from its cage at Kano Zoological garden. October 20, 2019 In "News" The authorities of the University of Ibadan have denied the rumour that two lions have escaped from their cages at the zoological gardens in the institution and are said to be on rampage. July 24, 2011 In "News"